The paper discusses a method for topic modeling using distributional semantics and word vectors, which are commonly used in natural language processing and machine learning. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the sub-categories of computer science that deal with these topics, such as cs.CL (Computation and Language), cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.IR (Information Retrieval), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.DL (Deep Learning). Among these, cs.CL is the most likely category as it specifically deals with the intersection of computation and language, which is the focus of the paper.
